  "prompt": "How do I report fake app on Appstore?",
  "response": "If you believe you have encountered a fake or fraudulent app on the App Store, you can report it to Apple by following these steps:\n\n1. **Open the App Store**: On your iPhone, iPad, or Mac, launch the App Store.\n\n2. **Find the App**: Locate the app that you want to report.\n\n3. **App Details**: Tap on the app to view its details page.\n\n4. **Scroll Down**: Scroll down to the bottom of the app's details page.\n\n5. **Report a Problem**: Tap on the \"Report a Problem\" link.\n\n6. **Log In**: You may be prompted to log in with your Apple ID if you haven't already.\n\n7. **Select Issue**: Choose the type of problem you are reporting. In this case, select options related to fraud, scam, or the legitimacy of the app.\n\n8. **Provide Details**: Fill out the form with details regarding why you believe the app is fake or fraudulent. Be as specific as possible to help Apple investigate the issue.\n\n9. **Submit**: Once you've completed the form, submit your report.\n\nAlternatively, if you are on a desktop browser, you can visit the [Report a Problem](https://reportaproblem.apple.com/) page directly, login with your Apple ID, and follow similar steps to report the issue.\n\nRemember, Apple takes reports seriously and will investigate the app, potentially removing it if found to be against their policies.",
